            "id": 4,
            "name_pali": "Puppha Vagga",
            "name_en": "Flowers",
            "summary": "This chapter uses the metaphor of flowers to teach about the impermanence of life, the importance of good deeds, and the fragrance of virtue that surpasses all worldly scents.",
            "verses": [
                {
