                    "verse_number": 44,
                    "pali": "Ko imaṃ paṭhaviṃ vicessati, yamalokañca imaṃ sadevakaṃ; Ko dhammapadaṃ sudesitaṃ, kusalo pupphamiva pacessati.",
                    "translation": "Who shall examine this earth, the realm of Yama, and this world with its devas? Who shall select a well-taught Dhamma word as a skilled person selects a flower?",
                    "commentary": "This verse poses a rhetorical question about who can truly understand the nature of existence and select the right teachings. The answer is the wise person who, like a skilled florist selecting the best flowers, can discern the true Dhamma from false teachings. The verse emphasizes the need for wisdom and discernment in spiritual practice.",
                    "story": {
