                    "story": {
                        "title": "The Story of Anathapindika",
                        "content": "Anathapindika, the great lay supporter of the Buddha, was a Stream-winner (the first stage of enlightenment). When he was on his deathbed, Venerable Sariputta visited him and taught him a profound meditation on the impermanence of all conditioned things. Anathapindika, though in great pain, was able to understand and practice this teaching immediately because his mind had been trained through his earlier attainment. Like a skilled person selecting flowers, he could grasp the essence of even the most subtle teachings. This ability to discern and apply the Dhamma is the mark of a true disciple in training."
