                    "pali": "Ovadeyyānusāseyya, asabbhā ca nivāraye; Satañhi so piyo hoti, asataṃ hoti appiyo.",
                    "translation": "Let one advise, instruct, and restrain others from wrong. Such a person is dear to the good and detested by the bad.",
                    "commentary": "This verse describes the duty of the wise to guide others. Those who offer good advice and help restrain others from wrongdoing are valued by virtuous people but disliked by those who wish to continue in their unwholesome ways. The wise person should not be discouraged by the dislike of the foolish but should continue to offer guidance.",
